This is an excellent crime drama. Interesting story lines, with believable characters. The eye candy ain't bad, either. The conclusion of each episode usually brings a surprise arrest. Just as in real law enforcement, there are few shootouts. This is more cerebral, with good attention to detail. The errors are few, and only someone in law enforcement or the legal profession would catch them. I can't imagine why some exec would pull the plug on a series that had more viewers than CNN. And, A&E isn't talking.
Whoever decided to end this series should be fired.
